1)  Casual:
given two integers
assign variable to integer
add integers
return the result

    Formal:
Start
Set variable = integer 1
Set variable2 = integer 2
set result = to integer 1 + integer 2
End

2)  Casual:
given an array of strings
iterate through the array
add all strings together and return value

    Formal:
Start
create variable to hold concatenation
iterate over array
add each iteration to variable
end

3)  Casual:
take an array of integers 
iterate over array 
only keep every other value
store those values in a new array

    Formal:
Start
iterator = 0
new array = []
while iterator <= array size
if iterator is even store value to new array
iterator += 1
End